WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:02.636
Previously
on "Training Day"...

00:02.670 --> 00:06.574
I need hard evidence
of Frank Rourke's corruption.

00:06.607 --> 00:08.476
Kyle: I went to see Jack Rawls
the other day.

00:08.509 --> 00:10.278
He represented Teflon.

00:10.311 --> 00:12.313
He claimed he was in the employ
of a dirty cop.

00:12.346 --> 00:14.748
Was it you?
And my dad?

00:14.782 --> 00:16.317
No.

00:16.350 --> 00:18.219
Patterson: I tracked the money
from Lockhart's fund

00:18.252 --> 00:19.620
as far as I could.

00:19.653 --> 00:21.389
She's paying a private
investigation firm in Mexico.

00:21.422 --> 00:23.224
Who the hell would Lockhart
be looking for in Mexico?

00:23.257 --> 00:25.593
Your name isn't Ivers.
I'd say you're CIA

00:25.626 --> 00:28.096
working in the Continental
United States.

00:28.129 --> 00:31.099
I don't know,
but it cost your dad his life.

00:31.132 --> 00:32.766
Back off
Billy Craig's murder.

00:32.800 --> 00:35.636
If you keep digging,
it's not gonna end well.

00:35.669 --> 00:40.108
Not for you,
not for anyone you care for.

00:41.142 --> 00:43.444
[ Coyotes howl ]

00:43.477 --> 00:46.714
[ Vehicles passing,
truck horn honks ]

00:46.747 --> 00:50.384
Frank:
You're gonna want to judge me.

00:50.418 --> 00:53.121
[ Crowd cheering ]

00:53.154 --> 00:56.257
When the media
gets ahold of this,

00:56.290 --> 00:57.725
when the worst scandal

00:57.758 --> 00:59.460
in the history
of the department breaks,

00:59.493 --> 01:01.362
when they're handing down
the indictments...

01:01.395 --> 01:03.264
[ Cheering continues ]

01:03.297 --> 01:05.799
...you're gonna hear my name
over and over.

01:05.833 --> 01:07.801
Accusations of brutality.

01:07.835 --> 01:10.404
Corruption.

01:10.438 --> 01:12.206
Murder.

01:14.508 --> 01:17.578
**

01:17.611 --> 01:20.114
And you're gonna want
to judge me.

01:22.450 --> 01:25.653
But, hey,
you've come this far.

01:28.589 --> 01:32.826
All I'm asking is...

01:32.860 --> 01:35.263
wait till you hear
the rest of it.

01:35.296 --> 01:38.532
I think you owe me that much.

01:40.834 --> 01:43.171
[ Siren wails in distance ]

01:47.908 --> 01:49.410
What's all this?

01:49.443 --> 01:50.844
Ivers said Boudreau
was stabbed, right?

01:50.878 --> 01:53.214
So how the hell did those
terrorists get close enough

01:53.247 --> 01:54.582
if Ivers was watching
his back?

01:54.615 --> 01:56.417
Ohh!

01:56.450 --> 01:59.153
'Cause Ivers
stabbed Boudreau.

01:59.187 --> 02:01.155
You really think
the special agent in charge

02:01.189 --> 02:02.723
of the FBI's L.A. office
was murdered

02:02.756 --> 02:04.725
by a renegade agent
from Homeland Security?

02:04.758 --> 02:07.528
Homeland Security might
carry Ivers on their books,

02:07.561 --> 02:08.796
but I think he's CIA.

02:08.829 --> 02:10.698
CIA can't operate
on American soil,

02:10.731 --> 02:13.201
so he's hiding inside
an agency that can.

02:13.234 --> 02:14.468
To what end?

02:14.502 --> 02:16.370
Ivers came to see
me last night.

02:16.404 --> 02:18.706
Told me to stop investigating
Billy's murder or else.

02:18.739 --> 02:20.474
Why would Ivers know
anything about my father?

02:20.508 --> 02:22.210
I don't know,
but he's about to tell me,

02:22.243 --> 02:23.577
even if he doesn't
know it yet.
[ Taser crackles ]

02:23.611 --> 02:25.313
Ivers isn't some gangbanger
you can scare

02:25.346 --> 02:26.714
into snitching
on his homies, Frank.

02:26.747 --> 02:27.848
Guy's a professional.

02:28.849 --> 02:30.718
He's the first solid lead
I've had in 10 years.

02:30.751 --> 02:32.320
[ Gun clicking,
bullets clinking ]

02:32.353 --> 02:34.888
I'll be damned I'm gonna
let him just disappear.

02:34.922 --> 02:36.390
Hang on.
Frank.

02:36.424 --> 02:37.691
If someone sent Ivers
to warn us off,

02:37.725 --> 02:38.892
that means
we're getting close.

02:38.926 --> 02:40.561
Something
we've brushed up against

02:40.594 --> 02:42.496
made these people
nervous enough to break cover.

02:42.530 --> 02:44.665
Ivers is the muscle.

02:44.698 --> 02:46.400
The real lead
is behind us somewhere.

02:46.434 --> 02:48.469
[ Gun cocks ]
Before we make
a run at Ivers,

02:48.502 --> 02:49.703
let me look back
and see what we did

02:49.737 --> 02:50.871
to trigger him
in the first place.

02:54.508 --> 02:56.577
Alyse: Kyle,
you know where I am on this,

02:56.610 --> 02:58.346
what I think
it's doing to you.

03:01.014 --> 03:03.317
I can't.

03:03.351 --> 03:04.785
I can't walk away.

03:04.818 --> 03:06.420
And what if you don't find

03:06.454 --> 03:08.389
the answers
you're looking for?
I have to.

03:08.422 --> 03:09.723
**

03:09.757 --> 03:11.859
[ Sighs ]

03:19.967 --> 03:21.769
[ Car alarm chirps ]

03:24.004 --> 03:27.408
[ Engine starts ]

03:27.441 --> 03:28.876
[ Body thuds ]
Man: Ow!

03:28.909 --> 03:30.544
Aah!

03:30.578 --> 03:32.313
[ Coughs ]

03:32.346 --> 03:34.482
[ Cries ]
Ow!

03:34.515 --> 03:35.849
Ow! Oh!

03:35.883 --> 03:37.685
I'm in pain!

03:37.718 --> 03:38.886
I'm in pain!

03:38.919 --> 03:40.288
Aah!
Get up.

03:40.321 --> 03:41.622
What you mean,
"Get up," man?!

03:41.655 --> 03:43.791
I'ma call
1-800-Accidentes, man.

03:43.824 --> 03:45.393
You just hit me
with a car, dawg!

03:45.426 --> 03:47.295
Unless you wanna fix this
another way.

03:47.328 --> 03:49.397
Couple hundred should do it
to the chiropractor.

03:49.430 --> 03:50.564
Yeah.
What you think?

03:50.598 --> 03:51.832
Guess again.

03:51.865 --> 03:54.268
Guess again?
G-Guess again?!

03:54.302 --> 03:55.636
Hold up, man.
Let me tell you something, man.

03:55.669 --> 03:56.804
I ain't playing here.

03:56.837 --> 03:58.472
I got --
I got whiplash, homie!

03:58.506 --> 04:00.007
It's all right up in here,
in this section, man.

04:00.040 --> 04:02.510
Whiplash is an injury
to the neck.

04:02.543 --> 04:03.811
Oh, yeah.

04:03.844 --> 04:05.279
Yeah, must be, uh,
back-lash, that's right,

04:05.313 --> 04:06.414
or something new
that just came out.

04:06.447 --> 04:07.748
You know what, man?

04:07.781 --> 04:09.049
Everybody's gotta make a living.
I get that.

04:09.082 --> 04:10.484
I do.

04:10.518 --> 04:12.786
But you picked
the wrong car, Ese.

04:12.820 --> 04:15.856
You didn't see
the government plates, did you?

04:15.889 --> 04:17.991
You must be new
at this game.

04:18.025 --> 04:20.060
Or stupid.

04:20.093 --> 04:21.929
[ Gun cocks ]

04:21.962 --> 04:23.431
[ Shotgun cocks ]

04:23.464 --> 04:26.434
Nah.
We got the right car, Ese.

04:26.467 --> 04:28.302
**

04:28.336 --> 04:30.471
[ Horn honking in distance ]

04:30.504 --> 04:32.773
[ Laughter ]

04:32.806 --> 04:34.942
-That's what so stupid about it!
-That's a joke.

04:34.975 --> 04:39.012
-It is stupid.
-[ Laughs ]

04:39.046 --> 04:43.751
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:43.784 --> 04:45.052
-Gentlemen.
-Yeah.

04:45.085 --> 04:46.620
Sorry to interrupt
your meal, but I --

04:46.654 --> 04:47.821
Then don't, rookie.

04:47.855 --> 04:50.090
I'm not a rookie.
I'm a detective.

04:50.123 --> 04:52.926
Oh. Pardon me, detective.

04:52.960 --> 04:54.695
[ Laughter ]

04:54.728 --> 04:56.530
Stan:
Yeah. You've got, what?

04:56.564 --> 04:58.866
Um...don't tell me.
No, no, don't tell me.

04:58.899 --> 05:00.768
Um...

05:00.801 --> 05:02.503
three years on the job?

05:02.536 --> 05:03.737
Maybe?

05:03.771 --> 05:05.506
[ Sighs ]
Two and change.

05:05.539 --> 05:07.908
[ Laughter ]

05:07.941 --> 05:09.610
Stan never misses.

05:09.643 --> 05:14.348
You're here about some wild-ass
conspiracy theory, right?

05:14.382 --> 05:18.619
Biggest case
of your short-ass career.

05:18.652 --> 05:20.921
[ Scoffs ] How could you
possibly know that?

05:20.954 --> 05:23.457
You're wearing it.

05:23.491 --> 05:24.792
It's all over your face.

05:24.825 --> 05:27.027
Stan: Hot on the trail
for some monster.

05:27.060 --> 05:29.129
Trying to open up
the lid of that coffin

05:29.162 --> 05:31.031
and put a stake
through the heart.

05:31.064 --> 05:32.966
[ Laughter ]

05:33.000 --> 05:34.535
Oh, well,
maybe I already have.

05:35.503 --> 05:36.637
You're Tim Wallace,
right?

05:36.670 --> 05:38.939
You were the first cop
on the scene

05:38.972 --> 05:40.908
at my father's murder.

05:40.941 --> 05:43.076
Detective Billy Craig.

05:43.110 --> 05:44.978
Boyle Heights, 2004.

05:45.012 --> 05:47.014
Don't act
like you don't remember.

05:48.115 --> 05:50.884
Give us a moment, okay?

05:50.918 --> 05:53.020
Come here.

05:56.957 --> 05:58.926
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:58.959 --> 06:02.129
Department wrote the whole
thing off as a botched robbery,

06:02.162 --> 06:04.398
but I know that was a crock,
a cover up.

06:04.432 --> 06:06.767
[ Scoffs ]
What, you think?

06:06.800 --> 06:08.101
Look.

06:08.135 --> 06:09.770
We were busting
your balls over there,

06:09.803 --> 06:12.906
but listen, your old man
was a good cop, Kyle,

06:12.940 --> 06:14.575
one of the best.

06:14.608 --> 06:15.843
Never doubt that.

06:15.876 --> 06:19.079
What they did to him
was wrong.

06:19.112 --> 06:21.415
Who's "they"?

06:21.449 --> 06:22.650
They.

06:22.683 --> 06:25.085
I mean, what, you want
names and addresses?

06:25.118 --> 06:27.421
'Cause I don't have 'em.
Nobody does.

06:27.455 --> 06:28.589
For good reason.

06:28.622 --> 06:29.990
Forget the guy
on the grassy knoll.

06:30.023 --> 06:31.459
These are the guys
who sent him.

06:31.492 --> 06:32.793
You know,
you climb high enough,

06:32.826 --> 06:34.695
you get to a place where
there's no difference

06:34.728 --> 06:35.863
between cops
and criminals.

06:35.896 --> 06:37.931
No nations, no borders.

06:37.965 --> 06:39.700
That's where
you'll find them.

06:39.733 --> 06:42.970
But, brother,
I wouldn't recommend it.

06:43.003 --> 06:45.138
What happened that night?

06:45.172 --> 06:48.008
[ Sighs ]

06:48.041 --> 06:50.678
I responded
to a shots-fired call.

06:50.711 --> 06:53.714
[ Siren wails ]
Your dad was dead
when I got there.

06:55.248 --> 06:56.917
You see anything?

06:56.950 --> 06:58.719
Something out of place?
A parked car? Anything?

06:58.752 --> 07:00.721
No, not a damn thing.

07:00.754 --> 07:02.856
Except Billy had written
something on his wrist.

07:02.890 --> 07:05.893
I always thought that it was
a partial plate or something,

07:05.926 --> 07:07.895
but the investigation
never went anywhere

07:07.928 --> 07:10.764
because somebody upstairs
didn't want it solved.

07:10.798 --> 07:13.734
[ Sighs ]
Whole thing made me sick.

07:13.767 --> 07:16.136
That's when I pulled
the pin.

07:16.169 --> 07:18.105
I work
private security now.

07:21.775 --> 07:24.712
You talk to Billy's partner?
He's got to know something.

07:24.745 --> 07:26.179
His partner?

07:26.213 --> 07:27.615
Yeah.
Frank Rourke.

07:27.648 --> 07:29.149
When I got there,
Rourke was with him.

07:29.182 --> 07:31.585
[ Sirens wailing ]

07:31.619 --> 07:33.053
[ Car door closes ]

07:33.086 --> 07:35.188
Wait. Frank was there
with my dad when he died?

07:35.222 --> 07:37.190
Mm.
He told me he was
at Hollenbeck and First.

07:37.224 --> 07:38.859
He was waiting for my father.

07:38.892 --> 07:41.662
Look, I don't know anything
about Hollenbeck and First.

07:41.695 --> 07:44.632
But Frank was with your Dad
when I pulled up, all right?

07:44.665 --> 07:46.199
Said Billy died in his arms.

07:46.233 --> 07:48.068
Then why wasn't Frank's name
in the report?

07:48.101 --> 07:49.537
You listed everyone else.

07:49.570 --> 07:51.271
Frank said that they were
off the books.

07:51.304 --> 07:53.874
I-I figured that he and Billy
had been out capering.

07:53.907 --> 07:56.710
W-Whatever they got up to,
it was none of my business,

07:56.744 --> 07:58.078
and I didn't want
any part of it,

07:58.111 --> 07:59.747
so I kept Frank's name...

07:59.780 --> 08:01.615
[ Gasps ]

08:01.649 --> 08:04.652
[ Screaming ]

08:04.685 --> 08:06.720
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]

08:10.724 --> 08:12.092
What,
are you Batman now?

08:12.125 --> 08:13.293
Nah, homie.
Hold up, man.

08:13.326 --> 08:14.862
Batman don't
kill people, man,

08:14.895 --> 08:16.964
or steal dope money
or plant evidence, or --

08:16.997 --> 08:18.165
Shut it.

08:18.198 --> 08:19.833
You know how
this works, Ivers.

08:19.867 --> 08:23.103
You want information.
I want off this building.

08:23.136 --> 08:24.672
How do we resolve this?

08:24.705 --> 08:26.974
We start by you telling me
who killed Billy Craig.

08:27.007 --> 08:28.676
Craig died 13 years ago!

08:28.709 --> 08:30.578
I was in Managua
at the time.

08:30.611 --> 08:32.713
No! No! No!

08:32.746 --> 08:34.247
Aah!

08:34.281 --> 08:35.816
You got to know
something.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.585
[ Strap creaking ]

08:37.618 --> 08:40.754
[ Panting ]

08:40.788 --> 08:43.957
Look, I'm a shooter.
I'm not a planner.

08:43.991 --> 08:47.327
They tell me where to go
and what to do, not why.

08:47.360 --> 08:49.563
I don't need to know,
I don't want to know.

08:49.597 --> 08:52.232
I told you, man,
they make the omelets,
I break the eggs.

08:52.265 --> 08:54.067
Poor choice of words,
Humpty Dumpty.

08:54.101 --> 08:55.068
No!

08:55.102 --> 08:56.737
No! No!

08:56.770 --> 08:59.206
[ Ratchet clicks ]

08:59.239 --> 09:01.775
Who are they?
Who sent you?

09:01.809 --> 09:03.076
What, you think I walk
into a big office,

09:03.110 --> 09:04.578
and M hands me a file?

09:04.612 --> 09:05.879
It doesn't work that way.

09:05.913 --> 09:08.982
There's cutouts,
redundancies.

09:09.016 --> 09:11.284
They don't want me to know where
the orders are coming from.

09:11.318 --> 09:12.886
Nobody gets the whole picture

09:12.920 --> 09:14.855
to prevent us
from giving it all up

09:14.888 --> 09:18.158
in the event some nutjob
dangles us from a rooftop!

09:18.191 --> 09:20.694
No! Aah! Aah!

09:20.728 --> 09:22.362
**

09:22.395 --> 09:24.164
I'm getting awfully tired
of holding this.

09:24.197 --> 09:25.966
Okay. Okay.

09:25.999 --> 09:27.334
Detective Craig has a key.

09:27.367 --> 09:29.169
They want it.
They've been after it for years.

09:29.202 --> 09:31.605
So you've been watching us.

09:31.639 --> 09:33.240
They thought
the key was lost forever

09:33.273 --> 09:34.675
until your dumbass partner

09:34.708 --> 09:36.043
started wearing it
around his neck.

09:36.076 --> 09:38.145
Then why not just kill us both
and take it?

09:38.178 --> 09:40.247
Because there's two.
There's two keys.

09:42.115 --> 09:43.316
It's a match set.

09:43.350 --> 09:44.785
They want 'em both.

09:44.818 --> 09:47.655
For what?
What do they open?

09:47.688 --> 09:49.322
That's way above
my pay grade, pal.

09:49.356 --> 09:51.258
Man: Hey, Frank.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.060
Didn't you say this guy
used to work for Home Depot?

09:53.093 --> 09:54.862
Homeland Security.
Homeland Security.

09:54.895 --> 09:56.664
[ Chuckles ]
Well, that's kind of funny, man.

09:56.697 --> 09:59.933
This right here says he works
at the State Department.

09:59.967 --> 10:02.335
[ Crowd chering, shouting ]

10:02.369 --> 10:05.605
**

10:07.708 --> 10:09.342
Frank:
He's with the State Department.

10:11.111 --> 10:13.346
We just killed a Fed, man.

10:15.148 --> 10:16.950
Tell your bosses
I don't scare easy.

10:16.984 --> 10:19.219
A deep voice
and a Kenny Loggins beard

10:19.252 --> 10:20.788
won't quite do the trick.

10:20.821 --> 10:22.322
I actually
feel sorry for you,

10:22.355 --> 10:24.224
you dumb son of a bitch.

10:24.257 --> 10:27.227
I was trying to do you a favor,
warning you off of this thing.

10:27.260 --> 10:28.729
[ Laughs ]

10:28.762 --> 10:31.231
You're gonna wish to God
you'd listened to me.

10:31.264 --> 10:32.966
[ Laughs ]

10:33.000 --> 10:34.067
Enjoy the ride.

10:35.035 --> 10:36.403
Aah!

10:38.238 --> 10:41.208
[ Clank ]
Aah! Aah!

10:41.241 --> 10:42.710
[ Strap creaking ]

10:42.743 --> 10:44.712
Aah.

10:44.745 --> 10:46.714
**

10:46.747 --> 10:48.749
[ Siren wails,
police radio chatter ]

10:58.191 --> 10:59.426
That's Agent Ivers' ID.

10:59.459 --> 11:01.829
I know.
I took it off of him.

11:01.862 --> 11:03.163
We don't want to know how,
do we?

11:03.196 --> 11:05.232
Probably not.

11:05.265 --> 11:06.767
So what's your beef
with Ivers?

11:06.800 --> 11:09.036
He told me to step off
of Billy's murder.

11:09.069 --> 11:11.138
So naturally,
you're gonna do the opposite.

11:11.171 --> 11:13.240
And that's an all-access pass

11:13.273 --> 11:15.442
to the State Department
Field Office.

11:15.475 --> 11:16.777
What are we looking for?

11:16.810 --> 11:18.178
Anything you can get
your hands on.

11:18.211 --> 11:22.049
So you want us to break
into a federal facility,

11:22.082 --> 11:24.051
impersonate
a government agent,

11:24.084 --> 11:26.186
and steal confidential
documents?

11:26.219 --> 11:27.921
Oh, hell, Frank,
I thought you were gonna ask us

11:27.955 --> 11:29.122
to do something stupid.

11:29.156 --> 11:31.191
There's a catch.

11:31.224 --> 11:33.260
Badge says State Department,

11:33.293 --> 11:35.328
but I think it's a CIA front.

11:35.362 --> 11:37.697
Well, that's not the catch,
Frank.

11:38.832 --> 11:40.067
That's the fun.

11:40.100 --> 11:41.468
[ Whitesnake's "Here I Go Again"
plays ]

11:41.501 --> 11:44.805
* Here I go again on my own

11:44.838 --> 11:46.406
[ Horns honking ]

11:46.439 --> 11:50.110
* Going down the only road
I've ever known *

11:51.845 --> 11:56.049
* Like a drifter,
I was born to walk alone *

11:58.351 --> 12:01.254
* And I've made up my mind

12:03.123 --> 12:04.491
* I ain't wasting no more time

12:04.524 --> 12:06.927
You know I can't stand
that stuff, man.

12:06.960 --> 12:08.195
[ Laughs ]

12:08.228 --> 12:09.963
Come on.

12:09.997 --> 12:12.465
Did a lot of panty-diving
in the backseat to this song.

12:12.499 --> 12:14.167
Well, don't get no ideas,

12:14.201 --> 12:16.136
'cause I ain't even really here,
man.

12:18.005 --> 12:21.108
So you wanna talk about
the dead elephant in the room?

12:21.141 --> 12:23.376
Do we have to?

12:23.410 --> 12:25.779
We both know
where you're headed.

12:25.813 --> 12:27.347
[ Sighs ]

12:27.380 --> 12:28.849
It was right in front of us
the whole time.

12:28.882 --> 12:30.383
We just didn't see it.

12:30.417 --> 12:32.519
* And I'm gonna hold on
for the rest of my days *

12:32.552 --> 12:35.088
Chasing this got me killed,
Frankie.

12:35.122 --> 12:38.358
I don't want my boy
to suffer the same fate.

12:38.391 --> 12:40.527
I won't let that happen.

12:40.560 --> 12:43.997
* ...along the lonely street
of dreams *

12:45.165 --> 12:48.101
* And here I go again
on my own... *

12:48.135 --> 12:50.270
[ Sirens wailing, horn honks ]

12:50.303 --> 12:51.504
How long have you known?

12:51.538 --> 12:52.873
I'm late for a meeting.

12:52.906 --> 12:54.141
I asked you a question.

12:54.174 --> 12:55.976
How long have I known what?

12:56.009 --> 12:57.144
That Frank was there
at the scene

12:57.177 --> 12:58.311
the night my dad
was killed.

12:59.546 --> 13:00.814
I suspected.

13:00.848 --> 13:02.282
Couldn't prove it.

13:02.315 --> 13:03.350
Who told you?

13:03.383 --> 13:05.018
You first, Deputy Chief.

13:05.052 --> 13:06.353
Did you knowingly
put me in the car

13:06.386 --> 13:07.888
next to the man
who murdered my father?

13:07.921 --> 13:10.423
I put you in a car
with Frank,

13:10.457 --> 13:12.559
hoping you'd bring me something
I could leverage

13:12.592 --> 13:13.894
to get him to tell me

13:13.927 --> 13:15.428
what he knows
about Billy's murder.

13:15.462 --> 13:17.998
And you've been
stringing me along

13:18.031 --> 13:20.367
because Frank
has got you twisted up,

13:20.400 --> 13:22.135
convinced
you need him.

13:24.304 --> 13:25.839
If you have proof

13:25.873 --> 13:28.575
that Frank lied about
his whereabouts that night,

13:28.608 --> 13:31.444
for the sake of your father,
don't keep it to yourself.

13:31.478 --> 13:32.913
So you can send Frank
to prison?

13:32.946 --> 13:35.248
So we can solve
Billy's murder.

13:35.282 --> 13:36.917
You signed off
on Water Street,

13:36.950 --> 13:39.052
knowing Frank and my dad
planted that gun on Teflon.

13:39.086 --> 13:42.522
Now, Teflon's dead,
my father's dead.

13:42.555 --> 13:44.591
Funny --
Frank's the last one

13:44.624 --> 13:46.126
who can testify
to your involvement.

13:46.159 --> 13:48.195
You better watch
your ass, boy.

13:48.228 --> 13:50.297
That's why you want him gone,
isn't it?

13:50.330 --> 13:52.199
It's not because
of my father's murder,

13:52.232 --> 13:54.868
it's because you're always
thinking beyond this desk.

13:54.902 --> 13:58.038
A political career, maybe,
and Frank could tank it for you.

13:59.639 --> 14:03.210
I'm bringing in Frank
on the murder of Billy Craig,

14:03.243 --> 14:05.145
based on a statement from

14:05.178 --> 14:07.447
a Confidential
Reliable Informant,

14:07.480 --> 14:11.018
"confidential"
being the operative word here.

14:11.051 --> 14:12.219
I won't cooperate.

14:12.252 --> 14:14.487
I won't play your games
anymore, Joy.

14:14.521 --> 14:16.089
Really?

14:16.123 --> 14:18.225
Did you ever
consider the fact

14:18.258 --> 14:22.029
that I'm the only one
who knows you're undercover?

14:22.062 --> 14:23.964
You're off the books.

14:23.997 --> 14:26.499
Far as the rest
of the world's concerned,

14:26.533 --> 14:29.869
you're just another rogue cop
in Frank's SIS.

14:31.004 --> 14:33.473
Now, bring Frank in,

14:33.506 --> 14:35.642
or go to prison
with the rest of them.

14:35.675 --> 14:38.378
It matters not to me.

14:39.646 --> 14:42.882
**

14:44.985 --> 14:47.520
[ Vehicles passing ]

14:47.554 --> 14:49.889
[ Mouse clicking,
computer beeps ]

14:52.225 --> 14:53.994
[ Keyboard clacks,
mouse clicks ]

14:54.027 --> 14:56.997
[ Printer whirring ]
[ Sighs ]

14:59.166 --> 15:00.400
Here.

15:02.702 --> 15:03.937
Let me help you with that.

15:03.971 --> 15:06.239
[ Chuckles ]

15:06.273 --> 15:07.540
[ Clears throat ]

15:09.309 --> 15:11.244
How do you know
how to do this?

15:11.278 --> 15:13.981
I've been tying Frank's tie
since I was 14,

15:14.014 --> 15:16.683
every time he went to court,
which was a lot.

15:16.716 --> 15:18.685
[ Chuckles ]

15:18.718 --> 15:22.589
**

15:30.197 --> 15:32.665
Yeah.
You clean up nice.

15:34.567 --> 15:37.304
[ Sighs ]

15:37.337 --> 15:39.406
[ Clears throat ]

15:39.439 --> 15:41.341
Not sure about the man bun,
though.

15:44.077 --> 15:45.345
You clear
on what you're doing?

15:48.148 --> 15:50.583
No.
I'm not, Bec.

15:50.617 --> 15:53.320
We're partners, right?
So that's all there is.

15:53.353 --> 15:56.589
You and me kicking down doors,
watching each others' backs.

15:56.623 --> 15:58.391
And I thought that would be
enough, I really did,

15:58.425 --> 16:00.060
but it's not --
Ah.

16:00.093 --> 16:02.529
I mean, are you clear
on what we're doing here?

16:02.562 --> 16:03.963
The mission.

16:05.098 --> 16:07.667
Oh, yeah.
Totally.

16:07.700 --> 16:09.069
[ Chuckles ]

16:09.102 --> 16:12.005
[ Clears throat ]
Good.

16:12.039 --> 16:15.275
Because getting caught doesn't
end in arrest, Tommy.

16:15.308 --> 16:17.177
It ends
with a 21-gun salute.

16:17.210 --> 16:18.745
Well,
I'm not gonna get caught.

16:18.778 --> 16:21.381
**

16:24.451 --> 16:26.086
This is Frank.
[ Elevator bell dings ]

16:26.119 --> 16:27.587
I don't check messages,
so don't leave one.

16:27.620 --> 16:28.621
[ Beep ]

16:28.655 --> 16:30.223
Hey.

16:30.257 --> 16:32.225
You wanna tell me
what the hell is going on?

16:32.259 --> 16:33.426
What are you talking about?

16:33.460 --> 16:34.627
Lockhart just asked me

16:34.661 --> 16:36.229
to assemble SWAT
to bring in Frank,

16:36.263 --> 16:37.497
which will likely result
in a massacre.

16:37.530 --> 16:39.166
She can do that?

16:39.199 --> 16:41.101
She's on the phone
with Judge Harrington right now,

16:41.134 --> 16:43.370
getting a telephonic warrant
for Frank's arrest

16:43.403 --> 16:45.505
based on some tip
from a confidential informant.

16:45.538 --> 16:47.107
And all this after you paid

16:47.140 --> 16:49.042
one of your weekly visits
to her office.

16:49.076 --> 16:51.244
You are not his trainee.
You are Lockhart's snitch.

16:51.278 --> 16:54.681
It's not that simple, Val.
My Dad was Frank's partner.

16:56.249 --> 16:58.518
This is about
your father's murder.

16:58.551 --> 17:01.354
Wait. You really think Frank
had something to do with it?

17:03.156 --> 17:05.092
I honestly don't know.

17:06.493 --> 17:09.662
Well, look, I am
a homicide detective, right?

17:09.696 --> 17:11.264
Maybe I can help you.

17:11.298 --> 17:13.533
[ Sighs ]

17:13.566 --> 17:16.103
I don't know
who to trust anymore,

17:16.136 --> 17:18.238
so I'm not gonna trust
anyone.

17:25.845 --> 17:28.348
**

17:28.381 --> 17:30.617
He give you anything?

17:30.650 --> 17:32.285
He's young.

17:32.319 --> 17:34.421
He's not stupid.

17:40.860 --> 17:44.063
**

17:49.169 --> 17:50.570
[ Beep, lock disengages ]

17:50.603 --> 17:52.272
Tommy: I'm in.
Rebecca:
What do you see?

17:52.305 --> 17:54.307
Nothing.

17:54.341 --> 17:56.143
Paint a picture
with words, dude.

17:56.176 --> 17:58.311
No, I mean,
literally nothing.

17:58.345 --> 17:59.712
No desks, no people.

17:59.746 --> 18:01.348
They're gone.

18:03.350 --> 18:04.851
Some black bag stuff, Bec.

18:04.884 --> 18:08.588
Whatever Ivers was doing here,
he pulled up stakes.

18:08.621 --> 18:10.557
He's getting ready
to go back underground.

18:10.590 --> 18:13.393
He's gearing up
for something big.

18:13.426 --> 18:15.195
We gotta find Frank.

18:15.228 --> 18:18.231
**

18:23.303 --> 18:25.338
Frank:
He called me that night.

18:25.372 --> 18:27.407
Said he had something
by the tail.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.609
I was supposed to meet him
at Hollenbeck and First

18:29.642 --> 18:31.711
in Boyle Heights.

18:31.744 --> 18:33.112
He never made it.

18:34.514 --> 18:36.216
[ Engine starts ]

18:36.249 --> 18:38.351
[ Tires squeal ]

18:38.385 --> 18:40.320
[ The Heavy's
"Short Change Hero" plays ]

18:40.353 --> 18:42.755
* Mm

18:42.789 --> 18:45.225
* Mm

18:45.258 --> 18:49.729
* I can't see
where you comin' from *

18:49.762 --> 18:54.367
* But I know just what
you runnin' from *

18:54.401 --> 18:58.505
* And what matters ain't
the who's baddest, but the *

18:58.538 --> 19:00.373
[ Tool thudding ]
* And I suffer

19:00.407 --> 19:03.376
* But I ain't gonna cut you
'cause *

19:03.410 --> 19:07.914
* This ain't no place
for no hero *

19:07.947 --> 19:12.519
* This ain't no place
for no better man *

19:12.552 --> 19:15.522
* This ain't no place
for no hero *

19:15.555 --> 19:16.623
[ Grunts ]

19:16.656 --> 19:18.225
Step away from the body.

19:23.696 --> 19:25.798
[ Exhales sharply ]
Put the gun down, Kyle.

19:25.832 --> 19:27.800
We got work to do.

19:27.834 --> 19:29.802
Come on, quit screwing around
and help me look.

19:29.836 --> 19:31.538
Look for what?

19:33.906 --> 19:37.644
**

19:37.677 --> 19:39.679
This.

19:42.249 --> 19:44.684
Go ahead.
Compare 'em.

19:51.791 --> 19:54.193
They're a match set.

19:55.862 --> 19:57.964
That's right.

19:57.997 --> 20:00.967
Now we can finally finish
what your old man started.

20:01.000 --> 20:04.203
**

20:08.541 --> 20:11.411
I just handed you the biggest
lead in your dad's case,

20:11.444 --> 20:13.913
and you're looking at me like
you got a load in your diapers.

20:13.946 --> 20:15.382
You lied to me, Frank.

20:15.415 --> 20:16.849
I know you were there
when my dad died.

20:16.883 --> 20:18.551
I didn't lie.

20:18.585 --> 20:21.321
I put my ass on the line
paving yellow bricks for you.

20:21.354 --> 20:24.291
I gave you Water Street.

20:25.458 --> 20:27.560
That was the beginning.

20:27.594 --> 20:28.861
The beginning of what?

20:30.430 --> 20:31.731
The beginning of the end.

20:31.764 --> 20:32.999
Your dad and I were convinced

20:33.032 --> 20:34.701
Teflon killed a cop
named Jeff Kern.

20:34.734 --> 20:38.271
I didn't know Kern well,
but he was one of us,

20:38.305 --> 20:40.673
so we weren't gonna let
Teflon walk.

20:40.707 --> 20:42.008
And we made damn sure
he didn't.

20:42.041 --> 20:44.544
[ Grunts ]
You killed a cop,
Teflon,

20:44.577 --> 20:46.879
which means
you're going away for good!

20:46.913 --> 20:48.681
[ Grunts ]
You can't put that on me!

20:48.715 --> 20:50.717
Hell we can't.

20:50.750 --> 20:52.619
Your prints are all over
the murder weapon.

20:52.652 --> 20:54.354
Plus all the gunshot residue.

20:54.387 --> 20:55.522
Aah!

20:59.392 --> 21:03.330
Lockhart signed off on
the report that put him away.

21:03.363 --> 21:05.031
**

21:05.064 --> 21:07.334
This is the last time.

21:10.069 --> 21:12.605
Teflon swore
he didn't shoot Kern.

21:12.639 --> 21:16.309
Told us some fairytale
about working for a dirty cop.

21:16.343 --> 21:18.778
Hell, we knew he had been one
of Alonzo Harris' informants,

21:18.811 --> 21:21.514
but Alonzo had been dead for
years when all this went down.

21:21.548 --> 21:23.650
So we just figured
Teflon was trying

21:23.683 --> 21:25.385
to sell us
some magic beans.

21:25.418 --> 21:27.520
But then Teflon's killed on
his first day at Twin Towers.

21:27.554 --> 21:29.789
Not killed,
assassinated.

21:29.822 --> 21:33.426
[ Screaming ]

21:34.527 --> 21:36.596
Got Billy thinking
that maybe old Teflon

21:36.629 --> 21:38.498
was telling the truth
after all.

21:40.433 --> 21:43.336
That's what brought him
to the Crypt Keeper here.

21:43.370 --> 21:44.637
Said he was gonna tell Billy

21:44.671 --> 21:46.473
what really went down
on Water Street.

21:46.506 --> 21:47.907
[ Crowd shouting, cheering ]

21:57.950 --> 21:59.386
Man: Come on, man!

21:59.419 --> 22:02.622
[ Cheers and applause ]

22:02.655 --> 22:06.593
[ Indistinct chanting ]

22:08.595 --> 22:10.830
[ Cheers and applause ]

22:12.932 --> 22:14.767
Come on!
Get him up!

22:14.801 --> 22:17.837
[ Shouting indistinctly ]

22:20.607 --> 22:21.708
Billy: Wait here.

22:21.741 --> 22:23.743
[ Crowd booing ]

22:28.615 --> 22:31.884
[ Shouting continues ]

22:35.755 --> 22:38.458
[ Cheers and applause ]

22:38.491 --> 22:40.593
[ Blows landing ]

22:43.496 --> 22:45.031
[ Crowd groans ]

22:48.034 --> 22:51.404
[ Cheers and applause ]

22:51.438 --> 22:54.841
**

22:54.874 --> 22:58.845
[ Shouting continues
in distance ]

23:17.630 --> 23:18.765
Let's make this quick.

23:18.798 --> 23:20.633
I got 50 bucks
on the little guy.

23:20.667 --> 23:22.902
You're the one asking around
about Teflon --

23:22.935 --> 23:25.705
gangbanger who killed that cop
down on Water Street.

23:25.738 --> 23:27.173
I don't care about Teflon.

23:27.206 --> 23:29.141
I want to know who killed
Officer Kern.

23:29.175 --> 23:31.744
I'm thinking the shooter's
still out there.

23:31.778 --> 23:34.046
[ Gun cocks ]

23:34.080 --> 23:35.582
Hey, you're good.

23:35.615 --> 23:36.983
[ Gunshot ]

23:37.016 --> 23:39.919
[ Casings clinking ]

23:39.952 --> 23:41.488
Should have seen that
coming.

23:41.521 --> 23:43.623
**

23:50.229 --> 23:52.665
Oh, hell, no.

23:52.699 --> 23:55.502
We just killed a Fed, man.

23:55.535 --> 23:57.136
Says here he's with
the State Department.

23:57.169 --> 23:59.672
State Department my ass.

23:59.706 --> 24:01.073
You saw how
he handled himself.

24:01.107 --> 24:03.543
This guy's a Spook.

24:03.576 --> 24:07.046
And he came here
to kill you.

24:07.079 --> 24:09.682
Brother, whatever this is,

24:09.716 --> 24:11.017
we don't want
any part of it.

24:11.050 --> 24:12.819
[ Crowd cheers in distance ]

24:12.852 --> 24:14.887
It's La Fraternidad.
They set me up.

24:14.921 --> 24:16.188
La Fraternidad?

24:16.222 --> 24:18.491
They put me in contact
with this guy, Frankie.

24:18.525 --> 24:21.093
Why's the cartel
in bed with the CIA?

24:21.127 --> 24:22.562
I don't know.

24:22.595 --> 24:24.063
But right now,
we got 300 people out there,

24:24.096 --> 24:25.932
so we sure as hell
can't move him.

24:27.934 --> 24:30.002
Then we won't move him.

24:33.606 --> 24:35.575
Frank: So we put
the body in the wall

24:35.608 --> 24:37.877
and agreed to forget
all about it.

24:41.581 --> 24:43.249
Only my dad
wouldn't let it go.

24:43.282 --> 24:45.718
Two weeks later,
he's calling me, frantic,

24:45.752 --> 24:47.053
asking to meet him here.

24:47.086 --> 24:49.188
Meet me at Hollenbeck and First.
Code 2 High.

24:49.221 --> 24:51.558
I got something by the tail
here, man, something big,

24:51.591 --> 24:53.259
and there's teeth
at the other end, man.

24:55.094 --> 24:56.262
You said he never made it.

24:56.295 --> 24:57.830
He didn't.

24:59.632 --> 25:02.168
By the time I found your dad,
he had bled out.

25:04.170 --> 25:06.606
**

25:06.639 --> 25:08.274
Why didn't
you tell me this before?

25:08.307 --> 25:10.142
'Cause you weren't ready
to hear it.

25:13.780 --> 25:16.515
He was coming back here
for the second key.

25:19.318 --> 25:21.287
But we still don't know
what they open.

25:21.320 --> 25:23.723
Take a closer look, rook.

25:30.062 --> 25:31.664
[ Exhales sharply ]

25:33.933 --> 25:36.102
The serial number's
not scraped off of this one.

25:36.135 --> 25:38.571
We can find out
what they open.

25:38.605 --> 25:41.574
Bingo.

25:41.608 --> 25:43.743
But first things first.

25:43.776 --> 25:46.045
We got to get rid
of this body again.

25:47.647 --> 25:50.182
Sorry, Kyle.

25:50.216 --> 25:52.551
Nobody gets out
of this one clean.

25:54.687 --> 25:57.289
On two.
One, two.

25:57.323 --> 25:59.626
Don't move!

25:59.659 --> 26:02.294
**

26:04.096 --> 26:06.565
Joy.

26:11.003 --> 26:13.606
Let me see your hands, Frank.

26:13.640 --> 26:15.041
Frank: Didn't know
you still carried a piece.

26:15.074 --> 26:16.208
Remember how to use it?

26:16.242 --> 26:17.777
Want to find out, sucker?

26:20.780 --> 26:22.248
You didn't check
for a tracker?

26:22.281 --> 26:23.716
I didn't think I had to.

26:23.750 --> 26:26.018
You're relieved of duty,
Detective Craig.

26:26.052 --> 26:28.020
It's the best
I can do for you.

26:28.054 --> 26:30.289
And you,
you're coming with me.

26:30.322 --> 26:31.357
On what charge?

26:31.390 --> 26:32.358
Murder.

26:32.391 --> 26:33.926
Lockhart, listen.

26:33.960 --> 26:35.628
You want to go down
as an accomplice?

26:35.662 --> 26:37.263
Leave the kid
out of this.

26:37.296 --> 26:39.265
You got no one to blame
but yourself.

26:39.298 --> 26:41.634
Yeah, how's that?
You had me sign off

26:41.668 --> 26:44.671
on that Water Street abortion
to cover your ass.

26:44.704 --> 26:47.039
You lied
about all of it.

26:47.073 --> 26:50.176
It wasn't Teflon who killed
Jeff Kern, was it, Frank,

26:50.209 --> 26:53.045
any more than Billy's murder
was a botched robbery.

26:53.079 --> 26:55.247
The same dirty cop
killed them both.

26:55.281 --> 26:57.650
That's what you think?

26:57.684 --> 26:59.318
You think I killed Billy?

26:59.351 --> 27:01.654
Teflon was
your unregistered informant.

27:01.688 --> 27:04.056
You had Billy
plant that gun on him

27:04.090 --> 27:05.324
to protect yourself.

27:05.357 --> 27:06.926
What, am I conscious?

27:06.959 --> 27:08.828
Billy kept digging,
didn't he, Frank?

27:08.861 --> 27:10.663
He wouldn't let it go.

27:10.697 --> 27:14.000
And you were afraid
that he'd work his way
back around to you.

27:14.033 --> 27:16.869
Find out that it was you
that had Teflon murdered.

27:16.903 --> 27:18.671
The Cartel killed Teflon.

27:18.705 --> 27:19.906
And you're the one

27:19.939 --> 27:21.808
who's been funneling cash
into Mexico.

27:21.841 --> 27:23.943
I know about
your slush fund.

27:23.976 --> 27:25.211
What are you paying for,
Joy?

27:25.244 --> 27:27.079
I was looking for answers,

27:27.113 --> 27:29.916
for your connection
to the head of La Fraternidad.

27:29.949 --> 27:31.150
[ Clatter in distance ]
Guys.
Stay out of this!

27:31.183 --> 27:32.819
El Jaguar?

27:32.852 --> 27:35.354
I nailed the guy's wife.
That's the connection, Joy.

27:35.387 --> 27:37.189
Beauty Queen.
Miss Jalisco.

27:37.223 --> 27:39.391
Ass like a couple of dogs
fighting under a blanket.

27:40.359 --> 27:41.794
Hey, you asked.

27:42.862 --> 27:44.196
Get away from the door!

27:44.230 --> 27:46.398
**

27:46.432 --> 27:48.701
[ Bullets ricocheting ]

27:48.735 --> 27:50.069
I'm assuming
they're not with you.

27:50.102 --> 27:51.838
Still a brilliant
detective.

27:51.871 --> 27:53.139
Then who the hell are they?!

27:53.172 --> 27:56.776
Don't think this is over
for one second, Frank.

27:57.844 --> 28:01.113
Over?
Hell, it's just getting good.

28:01.147 --> 28:03.783
**

28:06.152 --> 28:07.619
[ Gunshots ]

28:11.490 --> 28:13.125
Clear.

28:16.428 --> 28:18.264
What?

28:18.297 --> 28:20.366
[ Laughs ]

28:20.399 --> 28:22.334
Let's get the hell
out of here.

28:23.970 --> 28:27.006
**

28:39.551 --> 28:42.288
We got shooters
on the second floor.

28:43.522 --> 28:48.027
More coming
from the entrance.

28:48.060 --> 28:49.428
You take the catwalk,
Trainee.

28:49.461 --> 28:51.063
Try to keep 'em
off our backs.

28:52.198 --> 28:54.433
You ready?
Are you?

28:54.466 --> 28:55.968
Hell, yeah.

28:56.002 --> 28:58.905
[ The Black Angels'
"Young Men Dead" plays ]

29:06.913 --> 29:11.383
* Fire for the hills,
pick up your feet and let's go *

29:14.120 --> 29:19.091
* Head for the hills,
pick up steel on your way *

29:21.527 --> 29:26.398
* And when you find a piece
of them in your sight *

29:29.068 --> 29:33.873
* Fire at will,
don't you waste no time *

29:37.076 --> 29:43.182
* Another thought
of the unaware *

29:48.620 --> 29:50.422
[ Gun cocks ]

30:02.935 --> 30:04.136
Come on, Trainee.

30:08.307 --> 30:11.277
[ Screams ]

30:11.310 --> 30:12.544
[ Body thuds ]

30:12.578 --> 30:14.513
[ Breathing heavily ]

30:14.546 --> 30:15.514
**

30:15.547 --> 30:18.017
Thank you.

30:19.551 --> 30:24.490
* Run for the hills,
pick up your feet and let's go *

30:27.226 --> 30:31.063
* We did our jobs,
pick up speed, now let's move *

30:31.097 --> 30:32.932
[ Gun cocks ]

30:34.466 --> 30:39.571
* The trees can't grow without
the sun in their eyes *

30:41.908 --> 30:46.946
* And we can't live
if we're too afraid to die *

30:48.180 --> 30:49.181
Aah!

30:49.215 --> 30:51.150
* Hold on tight

30:51.183 --> 30:54.353
* Yes, hold on tight,
you're too slow *

30:58.925 --> 31:02.128
**

31:08.334 --> 31:10.602
[ Screams ]

31:18.610 --> 31:21.080
* Fire at the breeze
that blows *

31:21.113 --> 31:23.415
* These thoughts
through our minds *

31:25.952 --> 31:30.622
* Hire only thieves to steal
the thoughts from our heads *

31:37.296 --> 31:40.632
**

31:45.604 --> 31:47.539
[ Exhales sharply ]
[ Sighs ]

31:47.573 --> 31:49.241
[ Chuckles dryly ]

31:49.275 --> 31:51.477
Good as you remember?

31:51.510 --> 31:53.212
Nothing ever is.

31:53.245 --> 31:55.247
Having said that,
though...

32:02.654 --> 32:04.556
[ Breathing heavily ]

32:06.993 --> 32:08.560
My turn.

32:10.997 --> 32:13.966
Come on, come on.
Wakey, wakey. Let's go.

32:14.000 --> 32:15.434
Who are these guys?

32:15.467 --> 32:18.270
Well, they're not
the Salvation Army.

32:18.304 --> 32:21.640
Ivers, your kill team's
toast, pal.

32:21.673 --> 32:23.375
That the best you got?

32:23.409 --> 32:25.511
Ivers?

32:25.544 --> 32:28.680
Oh, those guys are just
the first wave, Frank.

32:28.714 --> 32:31.250
The Red Shirts.
Cannon fodder.

32:31.283 --> 32:34.220
And you were pissed I let her
put a tracker on my car?

32:34.253 --> 32:35.521
Ivers played you.

32:36.488 --> 32:38.257
He was after the second key
the whole time.

32:38.290 --> 32:39.525
You led him
right to it.

32:39.558 --> 32:41.627
What keys?
What is he talking about?

32:41.660 --> 32:44.263
Ivers: Okay,
here's the deal-e-o, Frank.

32:44.296 --> 32:45.764
You walk out with the keys,

32:45.797 --> 32:48.000
Kyle and Lockhart live
to tell the tale.

32:48.034 --> 32:50.169
However, I am not extending

32:50.202 --> 32:52.404
that opportunity to you,
you prick.

32:52.438 --> 32:54.040
I got a better idea.

32:54.073 --> 32:55.741
Why don't you nut up
and come up here in yourself,

32:55.774 --> 32:57.609
we'll settle this man-to-man?

32:57.643 --> 33:01.313
You think you're some kind of
latter-day gunslinger, Frank.

33:01.347 --> 33:03.482
You're just a redneck
with a drinking problem

33:03.515 --> 33:06.018
and a streak of dumb luck.

33:06.052 --> 33:07.319
But that's about to run out.

33:10.422 --> 33:12.458
[ Grunts ]

33:12.491 --> 33:14.260
She's hit!
[ Groans ]

33:14.293 --> 33:16.028
**

33:16.062 --> 33:19.498
Detective Craig, those are
some keen observation skills.

33:19.531 --> 33:21.300
She's gonna bleed out
if we stay here.

33:21.333 --> 33:23.169
[ Groans ]

33:23.202 --> 33:24.736
Come on.

33:24.770 --> 33:27.539
I'll be back in two shakes
of a lamb's tail.

33:28.840 --> 33:30.742
This is gonna hurt,
but I need you to get up.

33:30.776 --> 33:33.312
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

33:33.345 --> 33:35.514
Come on.

33:35.547 --> 33:38.050
Aah. Aah. Okay.
Okay, okay, okay.

33:38.084 --> 33:39.418
[ Both grunt ]

33:39.451 --> 33:41.653
I want to see
a cloud of pink mist

33:41.687 --> 33:44.323
where that bastard
used to be.

33:44.356 --> 33:47.826
[ Old West shootout-style music
plays ]

33:47.859 --> 33:51.263
* Oh oh, oh oh

33:51.297 --> 33:54.233
* Oh oh, oh, oh

33:54.266 --> 33:58.470
* Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh

33:58.504 --> 34:01.507
**

34:03.509 --> 34:06.645
Oh, you go to be kidding me.

34:11.250 --> 34:13.719
[ Bullets richocheting ]

34:27.799 --> 34:30.536
[ Truck horn honking
to the tune of "La Cucaracha" ]

34:31.537 --> 34:34.072
**

34:40.679 --> 34:44.516
[ Truck beeping ]

34:48.687 --> 34:50.256
Son of a bitch!

34:50.289 --> 34:52.858
[ Engine revs ]

34:55.927 --> 34:57.463
[ Music ends ]
I had him.

34:58.664 --> 35:01.400
Get the truck.
Lockhart's been hit.

35:01.433 --> 35:02.601
Lockhart?

35:02.634 --> 35:03.769
What the hell's
she doing here?

35:03.802 --> 35:06.538
**

35:06.572 --> 35:07.773
Careful with her.

35:07.806 --> 35:09.508
Easy.
Sit her down.

35:09.541 --> 35:10.742
Get her over here.

35:10.776 --> 35:11.743
Set her down easy.

35:11.777 --> 35:13.812
She's bleeding.
Easy.

35:16.315 --> 35:17.916
You didn't kill Billy,
did you?

35:17.949 --> 35:19.885
No.

35:19.918 --> 35:21.653
And you're not protecting
his killers.

35:21.687 --> 35:23.255
Unh-unh.

35:23.289 --> 35:24.856
[ Inhales sharply ]

35:24.890 --> 35:26.425
Then what are
we squabbling about?

35:26.458 --> 35:29.295
[ Exhales sharply ]

35:29.328 --> 35:30.762
[ Breathing raggedly ]

35:30.796 --> 35:32.764
Thank you, Frank.

35:32.798 --> 35:34.500
For what?

35:36.402 --> 35:37.936
I feel like a cop again.

35:37.969 --> 35:41.340
[ Sirens approaching ]

35:44.810 --> 35:47.813
Hang in there.
They're here.

35:55.887 --> 35:59.658
We need to find out what those
keys open before Ivers does.

35:59.691 --> 36:01.827
[ Sighs ]

36:01.860 --> 36:05.264
**

36:05.297 --> 36:06.598
I'm done, Frank.

36:07.699 --> 36:09.568
What do you want, Kyle?
An apology?

36:09.601 --> 36:10.869
[ Liquor pouring ]

36:10.902 --> 36:12.271
Five months I had
to ride around this city

36:12.304 --> 36:13.705
with my own personal
drill instructor

36:13.739 --> 36:15.407
berating me at every turn.

36:15.441 --> 36:16.708
And I put up with it.

36:16.742 --> 36:18.710
I went along with all
your crazy-ass schemes.

36:18.744 --> 36:19.945
I even covered for you.

36:19.978 --> 36:21.947
Because you made me believe
I needed you

36:21.980 --> 36:23.549
to solve
my father's murder.

36:23.582 --> 36:25.417
But you just walk into a trap

36:25.451 --> 36:27.453
because you won't listen
to me or anyone.

36:30.722 --> 36:33.692
Well, this is where I get off,
Training Officer.

36:33.725 --> 36:36.562
Thanks,
but I got it from here.

36:36.595 --> 36:37.996
[ Glass thuds ]

36:38.029 --> 36:39.331
I don't need you anymore,
Frank.

36:39.365 --> 36:40.599
Hey!

36:40.632 --> 36:42.768
You know what?

36:42.801 --> 36:44.303
I did lie when I said

36:44.336 --> 36:45.704
you had your father's magic
in you.

36:45.737 --> 36:47.906
You're nothing like him.

36:47.939 --> 36:49.207
Your Dad wasn't a coward.

36:59.518 --> 37:02.454
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
Hey! Wait!

37:02.488 --> 37:04.490
What the hell's
wrong with you two?!

37:06.492 --> 37:08.694
I should have turned you in
to Lockhart the day I met you!

37:10.496 --> 37:11.730
What does he mean
by that?

37:11.763 --> 37:13.632
Just mouthing off.

37:16.668 --> 37:18.404
**

37:18.437 --> 37:21.473
So Kyle was a spy
for Lockhart.

37:21.507 --> 37:23.642
Because I asked you
about him,

37:23.675 --> 37:24.943
and you straight-up lied.

37:26.678 --> 37:29.881
And I thought we don't
do that to each other.

37:29.915 --> 37:32.351
I was trying
to protect you.

37:32.384 --> 37:33.619
By exposing us
to Lockhart?

37:33.652 --> 37:35.354
I had to play the long game

37:35.387 --> 37:37.055
if I was ever gonna find out
what happened to Billy.

37:37.088 --> 37:40.526
Billy is gone!

37:40.559 --> 37:41.893
Tommy and I are still here!

37:41.927 --> 37:43.762
You should have told us,
Frank.

37:43.795 --> 37:45.897
That's not for you to decide.

37:45.931 --> 37:47.399
I'm your boss.

37:54.840 --> 37:56.608
I thought you were more
than that.

38:01.112 --> 38:05.083
What?
She's not my kid, Tommy.

38:05.116 --> 38:06.685
You can't treat people
like this, Frank,

38:06.718 --> 38:09.488
especially not her.

38:10.822 --> 38:13.325
You stay the hell away
from Rebecca, you hear me?

38:14.560 --> 38:17.563
She's already been
through enough.

38:20.632 --> 38:23.068
**

38:23.101 --> 38:24.870
[ Dog barking ]

38:31.977 --> 38:34.480
I'm sorry.
I-I should have called.

38:34.513 --> 38:35.981
[ Door closes ]

38:36.014 --> 38:38.450
What happened to you?

38:38.484 --> 38:42.020
I got in a fight...
with Frank.

38:43.154 --> 38:44.723
Okay.
Uh, sit down.

38:50.128 --> 38:52.798
I'm done with Frank.
I'm done.

38:54.900 --> 38:57.569
[ Inhales sharply ]

38:57.603 --> 39:01.006
I want to fix things.

39:01.039 --> 39:03.609
I want to be here for you,
for us.

39:06.144 --> 39:08.079
It's too late.

39:09.915 --> 39:12.584
**

39:12.618 --> 39:13.885
Baby.

39:13.919 --> 39:17.789
I'm staying at my mother's
for awhile.

39:20.091 --> 39:21.159
Wait.

39:21.192 --> 39:23.995
I'm tired of waiting, Kyle.

39:24.029 --> 39:25.797
I hope you find whatever
answers you're looking for.

39:25.831 --> 39:29.134
I really do.
[ Door opens ]

39:29.167 --> 39:31.169
Alyse.
I'm sorry.

39:35.040 --> 39:36.642
[ Scoffs ]

39:36.675 --> 39:38.710
**

39:44.182 --> 39:47.786
[ Nina Simone's "Don't Let
Me Be Misunderstood" plays ]

39:47.819 --> 39:52.057
* Baby,
you understand me now *

39:52.090 --> 39:54.092
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
Hey!

39:54.125 --> 39:56.027
What the hell's wrong
with you?!

39:56.061 --> 40:00.699
* If sometimes you see
that I'm mad *

40:00.732 --> 40:05.604
* Don't you know no one alive
can always be an angel? *

40:07.238 --> 40:12.177
* When everything goes wrong,
you see some bad *

40:12.210 --> 40:18.416
* 'Cause I'm just a soul
whose intentions are good *

40:19.217 --> 40:25.724
* Oh, Lord, please don't
let me be misunderstood *

40:28.494 --> 40:32.564
* Don't let me be
misunderstood *

40:32.598 --> 40:34.566
* I try so hard

40:34.600 --> 40:38.737
* So please, don't let me
be misunderstood *

40:40.872 --> 40:46.878
**
